Delhi Hospitals Hit by Coordinated Ransomware Attack

Multiple hospital networks in Delhi are experiencing significant disruption due to a coordinated ransomware attack. Patient data access has been severely hampered, and critical medical services are being affected. Negotiations with the attackers are reportedly underway, but data recovery efforts are complex. The ransomware encrypted critical patient records and operational systems. This incident underscores the vulnerability of healthcare infrastructure to cyberattacks and the severe consequences for patient care.